window.ChrisTheme.depthMapManager = new DepthMapManager();
```

### HTML Markup
```html
<!-- Any image can opt-in to depth treatment -->
<img src="photo.jpg" 
     data-depth-map="photo_depth.png"
     data-depth-intensity="20"
     alt="...">
```

### Ghost Integration
For Ghost content images, use a custom helper or post-processing:
```handlebars
{{!-- In post.hbs --}}
<figure class="kg-image-card">
  <img src="{{img_url feature_image}}" 
       data-depth-map="{{img_url feature_image}}_depth.png">
</figure>
```

## Motion Input (Shared)

Single MotionInput instance for all depth-map canvases:
```javascript
class MotionInput {
  subscribers = [];

  constructor() {
    // Mouse movement
    window.addEventListener('mousemove', this.onMouseMove);
    // Gyroscope (mobile)
    window.addEventListener('deviceorientation', this.onGyro);
  }

  subscribe(callback) {
    this.subscribers.push(callback);
  }

  broadcast(x, y) {
    this.subscribers.forEach(cb => cb(x, y));
  }
}
```

## Visibility Optimization

Each canvas uses IntersectionObserver to pause when off-screen:
```javascript
const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
  entries.forEach(entry => {
    const canvas = this.canvases.get(entry.target);
    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
      canvas.ticker.start();
    } else {
      canvas.ticker.stop();
    }
  });
}, { threshold: 0.1 });
```

## Fallbacks

1. **No WebGL**: Show static image (PixiJS handles this)
2. **Reduced motion**: Static image, no displacement
3. **No depth map available**: Show original image unchanged
4. **Mobile low-end**: Reduce displacement intensity or disable

